name: NSAccessibility.Subrole
desc: Values that describe specialized object subtypes that accessibility elements represent.

items.name: static let contentList: NSAccessibility.Subrole
items.desc: A subrole for content that is organized in a list, but is not in a list control or table view.

items.name: static let decrementArrow: NSAccessibility.Subrole
items.desc: A decrement arrow subrole (the down arrow in a scroll bar).

items.name: static let decrementPage: NSAccessibility.Subrole
items.desc: A decrement page subrole (the decrement area in the scroll track of a scroll bar).

items.name: static let definitionList: NSAccessibility.Subrole
items.desc: A subrole for a content list in a webpage.

items.name: static let incrementArrow: NSAccessibility.Subrole
items.desc: An increment arrow subrole (the up arrow in a scroll bar).

items.name: static let incrementPage: NSAccessibility.Subrole
items.desc: An increment page subrole (the increment area in the scroll track of a scroll bar).

items.name: static let sortButton: NSAccessibility.Subrole
items.desc: A sort button subrole for a table or outline view.

items.name: static let systemDialog: NSAccessibility.Subrole
items.desc: A system dialog subrole (a system-generated dialog that floats on the top layer, regardless of which app is frontmost).

items.name: static let systemFloatingWindow: NSAccessibility.Subrole
items.desc: A system floating window subrole (a system-generated panel).
